# Introduction
In this project we use time domain analysis to investigate some interesting features of some music tracks. These include, loudness, zero-crossing, windowing and spectral leaking, spectral centroids and spreads, spectral flatness, and spectral flux. We also go into some analysis of psychoacoustics such as a human's perception of frequencies and assigning these frequencies to a filterbank to use for future projects to analyse these music tracks further.

</div>

<div class="t m0 x3 h4 y3b ff1 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">

The current standard for high quality audio and DVD is a sampling
fre<span class="_ _14"></span>quency of f

</div>

<div class="t m0 xa h6 y3c ff1 fs4 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">

s

</div>

<div class="t m0 xb h4 y3b ff1 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">

\= 96kHz, and

</div>

<div class="t m0 x3 h4 y3d ff1 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">

a 24-bit depth for the quantization. The CD quality is 16 bit sampled at
f

</div>

<div class="t m0 xc h6 y3e ff1 fs4 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">

s

</div>

<div class="t m0 xd h4 y3d ff1 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">

\= 44.1 kHz.

</div>

<div class="t m0 x3 h7 y3f ff1 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">

</div>

<div class="t m0 x3 h4 y40 ff1 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">

The Nyquist theorem states that in order to
accur<span class="_ _14"></span>ately sample a maximum frequency of f

</div>

<div class="t m0 xe h6 y41 ff1 fs4 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">

s

</div>

<div class="t m0 xf h4 y40 ff1 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">

/2,

</div>

<div class="t m0 x3 h4 y42 ff1 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">

we must use a sampling frequency of f

</div>

<div class="t m0 x10 h6 y43 ff1 fs4 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">

s

</div>

<div class="t m0 x11 h4 y42 ff1 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">

. This means that we must use a sampling frequency of

</div>

<div class="t m0 x3 h4 y44 ff1 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">

240 kHz. As it is stated above, DVDs <span class="ff3">have a sampling
frequency of 96 kHz which wonâ€™t for </span>

</div>

<div class="t m0 x3 h4 y45 ff1 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">

dolphins. While there are likely other
technologi<span class="_ _14"></span>es that have a sampling frequency
of 240 kHz,

</div>

<div class="t m0 x3 h4 y46 ff1 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">

they are likely not cost effective, so it is not viable to share the
sounds of dolphins with the

</div>

<div class="t m0 x3 h4 y47 ff1 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">

typical consumer until better recording standards are developed.

</div>

<div class="t m0 x3 h2 y48 ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">

2.1) Segments, Frames, Sa<span class="_ _0"></span>mples

</div>

<div class="t m0 x3 h4 y49 ff1 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">

In order to automatically analyze the music, the audio files
are<span class="_ _14"></span> segmented into non overlapping

</div>

<div class="t m0 x3 h4 y4a ff1 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">

segments of a few seconds. This provides the coarsest resolution for the
a<span class="_ _14"></span>na<span class="_ _0"></span>lysis. The audio

</div>

<div class="t m0 x3 h4 y4b ff1 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">

features are computed at a much finer
resolution<span class="_ _14"></span>. The audio file is divided into
frames of a few

</div>

<div class="t m0 x3 h4 y4c ff1 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">

milliseconds over which the analysis is conducted. In some cases the
fram<span class="_ _14"></span>es may be chosen to

</div>

<div class="t m0 x3 h4 y4d ff1 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">

overlap, whereas in other cases they will not.

</div>

<div class="t m0 x3 h4 y4e ff1 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">

In this lab the audio files are sampled at f

</div>

<div class="t m0 x12 h6 y4f ff1 fs4 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">

s

</div>

<div class="t m0 x7 h4 y4e ff1 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">

\= 11, 050 Hz, and we consider i<span class="_ _14"></span>ntervals of
size N =

</div>

<div class="t m0 x3 h4 y50 ff1 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">

512 samples, or 46 ms. This interval of 46
millisec<span class="_ _14"></span>onds is called a frame. We will
implement

</div>

<div class="t m0 x3 h4 y51 ff1 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">

several algorithms that will return a set of
featur<span class="_ _14"></span>es for each
fra<span class="_ _0"></span>me. While there are 512
sam<span class="_ _14"></span>ples

</div>

<div class="t m0 x3 h4 y52 ff1 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">

per frame, we will usually return a feature
vector<span class="_ _14"></span> of much smaller size.

</div>

</div>

domain analyses. Below is the code used to

<div class="t m0 x3 h4 y208 ff1 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">

freqDist.m:

</div>

<div class="t m0 x3 hc y209 ff5 fs5 fc1 sc0 ls4 ws0">

function<span class="fc0 ls0"> <span class="ls4">\[ Xk \] = freqDist(
filename )</span><span class="fs3"> </span></span>

</div>

<div class="t m0 x3 hc y133 ff5 fs5 fc3 sc0 ls4 ws0">

%freqDist Computes the frequency distribution<span class="fs3 fc0 ls0">
</span>

</div>

<div class="t m0 x3 hc y20a ff5 fs5 fc3 sc0 ls4 ws0">

% info=audioinfo(filename);<span class="fs3 fc0 ls0"> </span>

</div>

<div class="t m0 x3 hc y20b ff5 fs5 fc0 sc0 ls4 ws0">

song=extractSound(filename);<span class="fs3 ls0"> </span>

</div>

<div class="t m0 x3 hc y20c ff5 fs5 fc0 sc0 ls4 ws0">

frames\_overlap = buffer(song,512,256);<span class="fs3 ls0"> </span>

</div>

<div class="t m0 x3 hc y20d ff5 fs5 fc0 sc0 ls4 ws0">

w=kaiser(512);<span class="fs3 ls0"> </span>

</div>

<div class="t m0 x3 hc y20e ff5 fs5 fc0 sc0 ls4 ws0">

N=512;<span class="fs3 ls0"> </span>

</div>

<div class="t m0 x3 hc y20f ff5 fs5 fc0 sc0 ls4 ws0">

Y=fft(w.\*frames\_overlap(:,2));<span class="fs3 ls0"> </span>

</div>

<div class="t m0 x3 hc y210 ff5 fs5 fc0 sc0 ls4 ws0">

Xk=Y(1:256);<span class="fs3 ls0"> </span>

</div>

<div class="t m0 x3 hc y211 ff5 fs5 fc0 sc0 ls4 ws0">

K=N/2+1;<span class="fs3 ls0"> </span>

</div>

<div class="t m0 x3 hc yf5 ff5 fs5 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">

<span class="fs3"> </span>

</div>

<div class="t m0 x3 hc y212 ff5 fs5 fc1 sc0 ls4 ws0">

for<span class="fc0 ls0"> <span class="ls4">i =
1:length(frames\_overlap)</span><span class="fs3"> </span></span>

</div>

<div class="t m0 x3 hc y18f ff5 fs5 fc0 sc0 ls4 ws0">

Y=fft(w.\*frames\_overlap(:,i));<span class="fs3 ls0"> </span>

</div>

<div class="t m0 x3 hc y213 ff5 fs5 fc0 sc0 ls4 ws0">

Xk(1:K,i)=Y(1:K);<span class="fs3 ls0"> </span>

</div>

<div class="t m0 x3 hc y214 ff5 fs5 fc1 sc0 ls4 ws0">

end<span class="fs3 fc0 ls0"> </span>

</div>

<div class="t m0 x3 hc y215 ff5 fs5 fc1 sc0 ls4 ws0">

end<span class="fs3 fc0 ls0"> </span>

</div>

<span class="_ _0"></span>

<div class="t m0 x3 hc y2d7 ff5 fs5 fc1 sc0 ls4 ws0">

function<span class="fc0 ls0"> <span class="ls4">\[ fbank \] =

Hp.<span class="fs3 fc0 ls0"> </span>

<span class="fs3 fc0"> </span>

<div class="t m0 x3 hc y2dd ff5 fs5 fc0 sc0 ls4 ws0">

bands</span><span class="fs3 ls0"> </span>

</div>

<div class="t m0 x3 hc y2a6 ff5 fs5 fc3 sc0 ls4 ws0">

% linear frequencies<span class="fs3 fc0 ls0"> </span>

</div>

<div class="t m0 x3 hc y2de ff5 fs5 fc0 sc0 ls4 ws0">

N=512;<span class="fs3 ls0"> </span>

</div>

<div class="t m0 x3 hc yeb ff5 fs5 fc0 sc0 ls4 ws0">

K=N/2+1;<span class="fs3 ls0"> </span>

</div>

<div class="t m0 x3 hc y2df ff5 fs5 fc3 sc0 ls4 ws0">

% fbank=zeros(nbanks,K);<span class="fs3 fc0 ls0"> </span>

<div class="t m0 x3 hc y2e0 ff5 fs5 fc0 sc0 ls4 ws0">

fs=11025;<span class="fs3 ls0"> </span>

<div class="t m0 x3 hc y2e1 ff5 fs5 fc0 sc0 ls4 ws0">

linFrq = 20:fs/2;<span class="fs3 ls0"> </span>

<div class="t m0 x3 hc y2e2 ff5 fs5 fc3 sc0 ls4 ws0">

<div class="t m0 x3 hc y2e3 ff5 fs5 fc0 sc0 ls4 ws0">

<div class="t m0 x3 hc yef ff5 fs5 fc0 sc0 ls4 ws0">

<div class="t m0 x3 hc y2e5 ff5 fs5 fc3 sc0 ls4 ws0">

<div class="t m0 x3 hc y2e6 ff5 fs5 fc0 sc0 ls4 ws0">

<div class="t m0 x3 hc y2e7 ff5 fs5 fc3 sc0 ls4 ws0">

% melIdx2Frq (p) =
<span class="ls0">\\</span>Omega\_p<span class="fs3 fc0 ls0"> </span>

<div class="t m0 x3 hc y2e8 ff5 fs5 fc1 sc0 ls4 ws0">

for<span class="fc0 ls0">
<span class="ls4">i=1:nbanks+2</span><span class="fs3"> </span></span>

<div class="t m0 x3 hc y2e9 ff5 fs5 fc0 sc0 ls4 ws0">

\[\~, indx\] = min(abs(melFrq <span class="ls0">-
</span>melIdx(i)));<span class="fs3 ls0"> </span>

</div>

<div class="t m0 x3 hc y27a ff5 fs5 fc0 sc0 ls4 ws0">

melIdx2Frq(i) = linFrq(indx);<span class="fs3 ls0"> </span>

<div class="t m0 x3 hc y2ea ff5 fs5 fc1 sc0 ls4 ws0">

end<span class="fs3 fc0 ls0"> </span>

filt\_val = filt\_val\*((fbank\_freq(j)
<span class="ls0">-</span>melIdx2Frq(i<span class="ls0">-</span>1))
<span class="fc1">...</span><span class="fs3 ls0"> </span>

<div class="t m0 x3 hc y19a ff5 fs5 fc1 sc0 ls4 ws0">

<div class="t m0 x3 hc y19b ff5 fs5 fc3 sc0 ls4 ws0">

%mfcc Computes the Mel frequency coeffecients<span class="fs3 fc0 ls0">
</span>

</div>

<div class="t m0 x3 hc y22d ff5 fs5 fc3 sc0 ls4 ws0">

% The mel<span class="ls0">-</span>spectrum (MFCC) coefficient of the
n<span class="ls0">-</span>th frame is defined
for<span class="fs3 fc0 ls0"> </span>

</div>

<div class="t m0 x3 hc y19d ff5 fs5 fc3 sc0 ls4 ws0">

% p = 1,...,NB<span class="fs3 fc0 ls0"> </span>

</div>

<div class="t m0 x3 hc y19e ff5 fs5 fc3 sc0 ls4 ws0">

% fbank=fbank/max(fbank);<span class="fs3 fc0 ls0"> </span>

</div>

<div class="t m0 x3 hc y19f ff5 fs5 fc0 sc0 ls4 ws0">

\[a,\~\]=size(fbank);<span class="fs3 ls0"> </span>

</div>

<div class="t m0 x3 hc y1a0 ff5 fs5 fc0 sc0 ls4 ws0">

\[c,d\]=size(Xn);<span class="fs3 ls0"> </span>

</div>

<div class="t m0 x3 hc y306 ff5 fs5 fc3 sc0 ls4 ws0">

% a should be 40<span class="fs3 fc0 ls0"> </span>

</div>

<div class="t m0 x3 hc y1a2 ff5 fs5 fc3 sc0 ls4 ws0">

% c should be 257<span class="fs3 fc0 ls0"> </span>

</div>

<div class="t m0 x3 hc y1a3 ff5 fs5 fc3 sc0 ls4 ws0">

% d should be num frames (1032)<span class="fs3 fc0 ls0"> </span>

</div>

<div class="t m0 x3 hc y1a4 ff5 fs5 fc0 sc0 ls4 ws0">

<div class="t m0 x3 hc y1a5 ff5 fs5 fc1 sc0 ls4 ws0">

frames</span></span><span class="fs3"> </span></span>

<div class="t m0 x3 hc y307 ff5 fs5 fc0 sc0 ls4 ws0">

mfcc\_val=0;<span class="fs3 ls0"> </span>

<div class="t m0 x3 hc y1a7 ff5 fs5 fc0 sc0 ls4 ws0">

<span class="fc1">for</span><span class="ls0"> </span>p=1:a
<span class="fc3">% banks</span><span class="fs3 ls0"> </span>

</div>

<div class="t m0 x3 hc y1a8 ff5 fs5 fc0 sc0 ls4 ws0">

<span class="fc1">for</span><span class="ls0">
</span>k=1:c<span class="fs3 ls0"> </span>

</div>

<div class="t m0 x3 hc y1a9 ff5 fs5 fc0 sc0 ls4 ws0">

mfcc\_val = mfcc\_val +
abs((fbank(p,k)\*Xn(k,n))^2);<span class="fs3 ls0"> </span>

<div class="t m0 x3 hc y1aa ff5 fs5 fc0 sc0 ls4 ws0">

<span class="fc1">end</span><span class="fs3 ls0"> </span>

</div>

<div class="t m0 x3 hc y308 ff5 fs5 fc0 sc0 ls4 ws0">

<span class="fc1">end</span><span class="fs3 ls0"> </span>

</div>

<div class="t m0 x3 hc y309 ff5 fs5 fc1 sc0 ls4 ws0">

end<span class="fs3 fc0 ls0"> </span>
